(:summary    "Align text to a specific column, by regexp"
 :created    "1999"
 :updated    "2011"
 :license    "GPL-3"
 :authors    (("John Wiegley" . "johnw@gnu.org"))
 :maintainer ("FSF")
 :provided   (align)
 :keywords   ("convenience" "languages" "lisp")
 :commentary "\
This mode allows you to align regions in a context-sensitive fashion.
The classic use is to align assignments:

   int a = 1;
   short foo = 2;
   double blah = 4;

becomes

   int    a    = 1;
   short  foo  = 2;
   double blah = 4;")
